    <text id="F4032T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McClure writes Slifer on behalf of James M. Sellers, a potential candidate for
                    State Senator.</p>
            </div1>

        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Confidential
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="-08-06"><abbr expan="August">Aug</abbr> 6th</date>
                        <name type="place">Repository &amp; Whig Office <lb/> Chambersburg</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear <abbr expan="Colonel">Col</abbr>-</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>James M Sellers wishes his name mentioned in the "Chronicle" for Senator, and he
                    and I will both esteem it a personal favor if you will have it done. I do not
                    know that he will be a candidate, but he wishes to be in a safe <hi
                        rend="underline">line</hi> for it should circumstances seem to demand him to
                    offer himself. </p>

                <p>Mr Sellers contributed greatly to your nomination in 1851, and did much to
                    sustain the nomination in the midst of threatened <pb n="2"/>dis <unclear/> of
                    the mal-contents. He visited Lewistown twice prior to the selection of their
                    conferees, once with myself, and earnestly urged the selection of confereees
                    favorable to yourself.</p>

                <p>He neither expects or desires you to take a stand for him, but he will be
                    gratified if you will have his name mentioned in a brief article. This is all
                    strictly <hi rend="underline">confidential</hi> of course. </p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Tr</salute>
                    <signed>AK McClure</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col</abbr> Slifer</name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
